[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1388},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication\u002F":1363,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2023\u002F10\u002F13\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication\u002F":1372},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20231013\u002F3280561145\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1347,"date":1348,"description":26,"extension":1349,"lang":1350,"meta":1351,"navigation":694,"path":1352,"readingMinutes":1353,"seo":1354,"standalone":1355,"stem":1356,"tags":1357,"tldr":1360,"updated":1348,"url":1361,"__hash__":1362},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fday-29-about-jwt-authentication.md","Day 29 - About JWT Authentication","3479708607",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1336},"minimark",[11,19,24,27,31,34,37,40,48,52,63,66,94,111,114,123,126,148,152,155,171,176,179,187,190,198,202,205,274,277,285,288,299,302,313,316,339,342,392,397,401,404,450,453,489,492,524,527,561,564,571,574,582,591,597,600,603,606,980,983,989,992,995,998,1002,1009,1028,1031,1126,1132,1143,1148,1151,1203,1210,1314,1317,1329,1332],[12,13,14],"p",{},[15,16],"img",{"alt":17,"src":18},"About JWT authentication","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fisray_notarray_web_Certification_87b4aacf-552a-40c1-8cb8-9fa5dca7d52d.png",[20,21,23],"h2",{"id":22},"intro","Intro",[12,25,26],{},"This post introduces JWT authentication. We haven't covered it before, but in real-world dev it's really important.",[20,28,30],{"id":29},"authentication","Authentication",[12,32,33],{},"Why authenticate? In previous chapters, we didn't actually do any authentication mechanism — APIs, Discord, Chrome Extension, etc. — none of it. So why authenticate?",[12,35,36],{},"Some features in what we develop are restricted to specific people — admins, VIPs, etc. So we need a mechanism to authenticate identity. That's where JWT (JSON Web Token) comes in.",[12,38,39],{},"Modern mainstream development uses frontend-backend separation, not the traditional SSR (Server Side Rendering) architecture. The frontend mostly gets data via APIs the backend provides — and this data fetching needs to be authenticated.",[41,42,45],"callout",{"title":43,"type":44},"Note","note",[12,46,47],{},"In the early days, after a user logged in, the backend would store the user's UID in the server's memory (Session). But because modern mainstream development uses frontend-backend separation, this approach doesn't apply anymore — hence JWT.",[20,49,51],{"id":50},"what-is-json-web-token","What is JSON Web Token?",[12,53,54,55,62],{},"JWT stands for JSON Web Token — a widely used standard for authentication and authorization, especially in web development. It's also an open standard (",[56,57,61],"a",{"href":58,"rel":59},"https:\u002F\u002Fdatatracker.ietf.org\u002Fdoc\u002Fhtml\u002Frfc7519",[60],"nofollow","RFC 7519",").",[12,64,65],{},"JWT structure has three parts:",[67,68,69,78,86],"ul",{},[70,71,72,73],"li",{},"HEADER: ALGORITHM & TOKEN TYPE\n",[67,74,75],{},[70,76,77],{},"Indicates what algorithm encrypts this Token, and the Token type",[70,79,80,81],{},"PAYLOAD: DATA\n",[67,82,83],{},[70,84,85],{},"Mainly stores data — user ID, name, etc.",[70,87,88,89],{},"VERIFY SIGNATURE\n",[67,90,91],{},[70,92,93],{},"Used to verify the Token is correct",[95,96,101],"pre",{"className":97,"code":98,"language":99,"meta":100,"style":100},"language-txt shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIxMjM0NTY3ODkwIiwibmFtZSI6IkpvaG4gRG9lIiwiaWF0IjoxNTE2MjM5MDIyfQ.SflKxwRJSMeKKF2QT4fwpMeJf36POk6yJV_adQssw5c\n","txt","",[102,103,104],"code",{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,106,109],"span",{"class":107,"line":108},"line",1,[105,110,98],{},[12,112,113],{},"Hard to see the difference right? Breaking it down by structure:",[95,115,117],{"className":97,"code":116,"language":99,"meta":100,"style":100},"HEADER.PAYLOAD.VERIFY SIGNATURE\n",[102,118,119],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,120,121],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,122,116],{},[12,124,125],{},"With the JWT example above, it becomes:",[95,127,129],{"className":97,"code":128,"language":99,"meta":100,"style":100},"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.  # HEADER\neyJzdWIiOiIxMjM0NTY3ODkwIiwibmFtZSI6IkpvaG4gRG9lIiwiaWF0IjoxNTE2MjM5MDIyfQ. # PAYLOAD\nSflKxwRJSMeKKF2QT4fwpMeJf36POk6yJV_adQssw5c # VERIFY SIGNATURE\n",[102,130,131,136,142],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,132,133],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,134,135],{},"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.  # HEADER\n",[105,137,139],{"class":107,"line":138},2,[105,140,141],{},"eyJzdWIiOiIxMjM0NTY3ODkwIiwibmFtZSI6IkpvaG4gRG9lIiwiaWF0IjoxNTE2MjM5MDIyfQ. # PAYLOAD\n",[105,143,145],{"class":107,"line":144},3,[105,146,147],{},"SflKxwRJSMeKKF2QT4fwpMeJf36POk6yJV_adQssw5c # VERIFY SIGNATURE\n",[20,149,151],{"id":150},"jwt-principles","JWT principles",[12,153,154],{},"How is JWT implemented? I mentioned the structure has three parts. The more core parts are PAYLOAD and VERIFY SIGNATURE. But let's go through all three. The example here uses the JWT Token from earlier:",[95,156,157],{"className":97,"code":128,"language":99,"meta":100,"style":100},[102,158,159,163,167],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,160,161],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,162,135],{},[105,164,165],{"class":107,"line":138},[105,166,141],{},[105,168,169],{"class":107,"line":144},[105,170,147],{},[172,173,175],"h3",{"id":174},"header","HEADER",[12,177,178],{},"HEADER mainly combines two parts:",[67,180,181,184],{},[70,182,183],{},"alg (Algorithm): encryption algorithm",[70,185,186],{},"typ (Type): Token type",[12,188,189],{},"These two parts get encoded into a Base64 string:",[95,191,192],{"className":97,"code":135,"language":99,"meta":100,"style":100},[102,193,194],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,195,196],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,197,135],{},[172,199,201],{"id":200},"payload","PAYLOAD",[12,203,204],{},"PAYLOAD is just a JSON object:",[95,206,210],{"className":207,"code":208,"language":209,"meta":100,"style":100},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","{\n  \"username\": \"Ray\", \u002F\u002F Username\n  \"email\": \"example.com\", \u002F\u002F Email\n  \"iat\": 1516239022 \u002F\u002F Issued At time\n}\n","json",[102,211,212,218,238,253,268],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,213,214],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,215,217],{"class":216},"s8XSl","{\n",[105,219,220,224,227,231,234],{"class":107,"line":138},[105,221,223],{"class":222},"sWTrB","  \"username\"",[105,225,226],{"class":216},": ",[105,228,230],{"class":229},"sWayO","\"Ray\"",[105,232,233],{"class":216},", ",[105,235,237],{"class":236},"sGBqm","\u002F\u002F Username\n",[105,239,240,243,245,248,250],{"class":107,"line":144},[105,241,242],{"class":222},"  \"email\"",[105,244,226],{"class":216},[105,246,247],{"class":229},"\"example.com\"",[105,249,233],{"class":216},[105,251,252],{"class":236},"\u002F\u002F Email\n",[105,254,256,259,261,265],{"class":107,"line":255},4,[105,257,258],{"class":222},"  \"iat\"",[105,260,226],{"class":216},[105,262,264],{"class":263},"stw71","1516239022",[105,266,267],{"class":236}," \u002F\u002F Issued At time\n",[105,269,271],{"class":107,"line":270},5,[105,272,273],{"class":216},"}\n",[12,275,276],{},"This JSON object gets encoded into Base64:",[95,278,279],{"className":97,"code":141,"language":99,"meta":100,"style":100},[102,280,281],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,282,283],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,284,141],{},[12,286,287],{},"PAYLOAD seems pretty simple right? But it's actually composed of three parts:",[67,289,290,293,296],{},[70,291,292],{},"Registered Claim",[70,294,295],{},"Public Claim",[70,297,298],{},"Private Claim",[12,300,301],{},"All three parts are optional, but in practice we usually use Public Claim to store data — user ID, name, etc.",[12,303,304,305,308,309,312],{},"Common settings include ",[102,306,307],{},"iat"," (Issued At) and ",[102,310,311],{},"exp"," (Expiration Time) in Registered Claim — these can be used to verify Token expiration.",[12,314,315],{},"Registered Claim has many properties:",[67,317,318,321,324,327,330,333,336],{},[70,319,320],{},"iss (Issuer)",[70,322,323],{},"sub (Subject)",[70,325,326],{},"aud (Audience)",[70,328,329],{},"exp (Expiration Time)",[70,331,332],{},"nbf (Not Before)",[70,334,335],{},"iat (Issued At)",[70,337,338],{},"jti (JWT ID)",[12,340,341],{},"So with the JSON object above:",[95,343,345],{"className":207,"code":344,"language":209,"meta":100,"style":100},"{\n  \"username\": \"Ray\", \u002F\u002F Username => Public Claim\n  \"email\": \"example.com\", \u002F\u002F Email => Public Claim\n  \"iat\": 1516239022 \u002F\u002F Issued At => Registered Claim\n}\n",[102,346,347,351,364,377,388],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,348,349],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,350,217],{"class":216},[105,352,353,355,357,359,361],{"class":107,"line":138},[105,354,223],{"class":222},[105,356,226],{"class":216},[105,358,230],{"class":229},[105,360,233],{"class":216},[105,362,363],{"class":236},"\u002F\u002F Username => Public Claim\n",[105,365,366,368,370,372,374],{"class":107,"line":144},[105,367,242],{"class":222},[105,369,226],{"class":216},[105,371,247],{"class":229},[105,373,233],{"class":216},[105,375,376],{"class":236},"\u002F\u002F Email => Public Claim\n",[105,378,379,381,383,385],{"class":107,"line":255},[105,380,258],{"class":222},[105,382,226],{"class":216},[105,384,264],{"class":263},[105,386,387],{"class":236}," \u002F\u002F Issued At => Registered Claim\n",[105,389,390],{"class":107,"line":270},[105,391,273],{"class":216},[41,393,394],{"title":43,"type":44},[12,395,396],{},"Note Claim is only three letters. Because JWT is designed to be concise and lightweight, Claim is only three letters.",[172,398,400],{"id":399},"verify-signature","VERIFY SIGNATURE",[12,402,403],{},"VERIFY SIGNATURE is encoding PAYLOAD and HEADER, then encrypting:",[95,405,409],{"className":406,"code":407,"language":408,"meta":100,"style":100},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","HMACSHA256(\n  base64UrlEncode(header) + \".\" +\n  base64UrlEncode(payload),\n  secret)\n","js",[102,410,411,420,438,445],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,412,413,417],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,414,416],{"class":415},"scAaK","HMACSHA256",[105,418,419],{"class":216},"(\n",[105,421,422,425,428,432,435],{"class":107,"line":138},[105,423,424],{"class":415},"  base64UrlEncode",[105,426,427],{"class":216},"(header) ",[105,429,431],{"class":430},"sOudu","+",[105,433,434],{"class":229}," \".\"",[105,436,437],{"class":430}," +\n",[105,439,440,442],{"class":107,"line":144},[105,441,424],{"class":415},[105,443,444],{"class":216},"(payload),\n",[105,446,447],{"class":107,"line":255},[105,448,449],{"class":216},"  secret)\n",[12,451,452],{},"How does JWT know which algorithm to use for encryption? Through HEADER:",[95,454,456],{"className":207,"code":455,"language":209,"meta":100,"style":100},"{\n  \"alg\": \"HS256\",\n  \"typ\": \"JWT\"\n}\n",[102,457,458,462,475,485],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,459,460],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,461,217],{"class":216},[105,463,464,467,469,472],{"class":107,"line":138},[105,465,466],{"class":222},"  \"alg\"",[105,468,226],{"class":216},[105,470,471],{"class":229},"\"HS256\"",[105,473,474],{"class":216},",\n",[105,476,477,480,482],{"class":107,"line":144},[105,478,479],{"class":222},"  \"typ\"",[105,481,226],{"class":216},[105,483,484],{"class":229},"\"JWT\"\n",[105,486,487],{"class":107,"line":255},[105,488,273],{"class":216},[12,490,491],{},"If using PS256:",[95,493,495],{"className":207,"code":494,"language":209,"meta":100,"style":100},"{\n  \"alg\": \"PS256\",\n  \"typ\": \"JWT\"\n}\n",[102,496,497,501,512,520],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,498,499],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,500,217],{"class":216},[105,502,503,505,507,510],{"class":107,"line":138},[105,504,466],{"class":222},[105,506,226],{"class":216},[105,508,509],{"class":229},"\"PS256\"",[105,511,474],{"class":216},[105,513,514,516,518],{"class":107,"line":144},[105,515,479],{"class":222},[105,517,226],{"class":216},[105,519,484],{"class":229},[105,521,522],{"class":107,"line":255},[105,523,273],{"class":216},[12,525,526],{},"Then PAYLOAD and HEADER get encoded and encrypted:",[95,528,530],{"className":406,"code":529,"language":408,"meta":100,"style":100},"PS256(\n  base64UrlEncode(header) + \".\" +\n  base64UrlEncode(payload),\n  secret)\n",[102,531,532,539,551,557],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,533,534,537],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,535,536],{"class":415},"PS256",[105,538,419],{"class":216},[105,540,541,543,545,547,549],{"class":107,"line":138},[105,542,424],{"class":415},[105,544,427],{"class":216},[105,546,431],{"class":430},[105,548,434],{"class":229},[105,550,437],{"class":430},[105,552,553,555],{"class":107,"line":144},[105,554,424],{"class":415},[105,556,444],{"class":216},[105,558,559],{"class":107,"line":255},[105,560,449],{"class":216},[12,562,563],{},"This encrypted string also gets Base64-encoded.",[12,565,566,567,570],{},"What's ",[102,568,569],{},"secret","? A private key. When we generate a JWT Token, we need a private key to encrypt. When we verify a JWT Token, we need this private key to decrypt.",[12,572,573],{},"Another question — our generated JWT Token:",[95,575,576],{"className":97,"code":98,"language":99,"meta":100,"style":100},[102,577,578],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,579,580],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,581,98],{},[12,583,584,585,590],{},"You can throw this at ",[56,586,589],{"href":587,"rel":588},"https:\u002F\u002Fjwt.io\u002F",[60],"jwt.io"," and you'll find it auto-parses and tells you what algorithm encrypted this Token and the Token type:",[12,592,593],{},[15,594],{"alt":595,"src":596},"JWT Token","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002Fjwt_token.png",[12,598,599],{},"OK problem:",[12,601,602],{},"\"Why can it parse without us providing the private key (secret)?\"",[12,604,605],{},"Because JWT Token is just Base64-encoded — not encrypted. So you can write your own JWT Token parser. Here's a simple example:",[95,607,609],{"className":406,"code":608,"language":408,"meta":100,"style":100},"\u002F\u002F Base64 decode\nconst Base64decoded = (str) => {\n  str = str.replace(\u002F-\u002Fg, '+').replace(\u002F_\u002Fg, '\u002F');\n\n  \u002F\u002F Pad with \"=\" if length isn't a multiple of 4\n  while (str.length % 4 !== 0) {\n    str += '=';\n  }\n\n  return window.atob(str);\n}\n\n\u002F\u002F Parse JWT Token\nconst jwtTokenEncoded = (str) => {\n  if(!str) return console.log('Please input JWT Token');\n  const [header, payload, signature] = str.split('.');\n\n  const headerDecoded = JSON.parse(Base64decoded(header));\n  const payloadDecoded = JSON.parse(Base64decoded(payload));\n\n  return {\n    header: headerDecoded,\n    payload: payloadDecoded,\n  }\n}\n\njwtTokenEncoded('eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIxMjM0NTY3ODkwIiwibmFtZSI6IkpvaG4gRG9lIiwiaWF0IjoxNTE2MjM5MDIyfQ.SflKxwRJSMeKKF2QT4fwpMeJf36POk6yJV_adQssw5c')\n",[102,610,611,616,643,690,696,701,728,743,749,754,769,774,779,785,805,835,872,877,904,927,932,939,945,951,956,961,966],{"__ignoreMap":100},[105,612,613],{"class":107,"line":108},[105,614,615],{"class":236},"\u002F\u002F Base64 decode\n",[105,617,618,621,624,627,630,634,637,640],{"class":107,"line":138},[105,619,620],{"class":430},"const",[105,622,623],{"class":415}," Base64decoded",[105,625,626],{"class":430}," =",[105,628,629],{"class":216}," (",[105,631,633],{"class":632},"syBk-","str",[105,635,636],{"class":216},") ",[105,638,639],{"class":430},"=>",[105,641,642],{"class":216}," {\n",[105,644,645,648,651,654,657,660,663,666,668,671,673,675,677,680,682,684,687],{"class":107,"line":144},[105,646,647],{"class":216},"  str ",[105,649,650],{"class":430},"=",[105,652,653],{"class":216}," str.",[105,655,656],{"class":415},"replace",[105,658,659],{"class":216},"(",[105,661,662],{"class":229},"\u002F-\u002F",[105,664,665],{"class":430},"g",[105,667,233],{"class":216},[105,669,670],{"class":229},"'+'",[105,672,62],{"class":216},[105,674,656],{"class":415},[105,676,659],{"class":216},[105,678,679],{"class":229},"\u002F_\u002F",[105,681,665],{"class":430},[105,683,233],{"class":216},[105,685,686],{"class":229},"'\u002F'",[105,688,689],{"class":216},");\n",[105,691,692],{"class":107,"line":255},[105,693,695],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":694},true,"\n",[105,697,698],{"class":107,"line":270},[105,699,700],{"class":236},"  \u002F\u002F Pad with \"=\" if length isn't a multiple of 4\n",[105,702,704,707,710,713,716,719,722,725],{"class":107,"line":703},6,[105,705,706],{"class":430},"  while",[105,708,709],{"class":216}," (str.",[105,711,712],{"class":263},"length",[105,714,715],{"class":430}," %",[105,717,718],{"class":263}," 4",[105,720,721],{"class":430}," !==",[105,723,724],{"class":263}," 0",[105,726,727],{"class":216},") {\n",[105,729,731,734,737,740],{"class":107,"line":730},7,[105,732,733],{"class":216},"    str ",[105,735,736],{"class":430},"+=",[105,738,739],{"class":229}," '='",[105,741,742],{"class":216},";\n",[105,744,746],{"class":107,"line":745},8,[105,747,748],{"class":216},"  }\n",[105,750,752],{"class":107,"line":751},9,[105,753,695],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":694},[105,755,757,760,763,766],{"class":107,"line":756},10,[105,758,759],{"class":430},"  return",[105,761,762],{"class":216}," window.",[105,764,765],{"class":415},"atob",[105,767,768],{"class":216},"(str);\n",[105,770,772],{"class":107,"line":771},11,[105,773,273],{"class":216},[105,775,777],{"class":107,"line":776},12,[105,778,695],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":694},[105,780,782],{"class":107,"line":781},13,[105,783,784],{"class":236},"\u002F\u002F Parse 